<br>
TOTAL: 40 Cards    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok here are the tweaks this time - same basic strategy, but I dropped the Warlum as I no longer need to search for quills/dancers etc, added Flutter Yups (INSANE vs ParaCape or another Shimmer deck), replaced a Shockwave with an Equilibrate (also great vs ParaCape, Shimmer mirror match, Weave, etc...), added Alaban Gloves as a reusable source of removal or extra energy on my magi before a Cataclysm, and a Drought. Drought is BRUTAL in this deck - looking to find room for a 2nd. If I can Drought while on Shimmer with a Storm Shield going, it&#39;s like a Time Walk! (yes, I&#39;m an old school Magic player) It can also buy me the time I need to hold off an opposing Cataclysm or Ormagon, letting me sacrifice the Pharan/Narths to keep Shimmer alive and still gain energy advantage. So far this deck is 18-2 in local tournaments, beating Van&#39;s new Akido deck and Dr. Bob&#39;s Shimmer mirror match, as well as a very good local ParaCape deck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
